  "prompt": "What are some examples of websites with great design?",
  "response": "There are countless websites with exceptional design, but here are some notable examples across various categories that are widely praised for their creativity, functionality, and aesthetics:\n\n---\n\n### **Portfolio and Creative Websites**\n1. **Awwwards** (https://www.awwwards.com/)  \n   - A showcase of the best-designed websites, often featuring cutting-edge design trends.\n   \n2. **Jessica Walsh** (https://andwalsh.com/)  \n   - The portfolio of a renowned designer, featuring bold, colorful, and interactive designs.\n\n3. **Studio Feixen** (https://stefan-huber.ch/)  \n   - A Swiss design studio with a playful, experimental, and typography-heavy website.\n\n---\n\n### **E-Commerce**\n4. **Glossier** (https://www.glossier.com/)  \n   - Known for its clean, minimalist design and user-friendly interface that reflects the brand\u2019s aesthetic.\n\n5. **Allbirds** (https://www.allbirds.com/)  \n   - A sustainable shoe brand with a simple, earthy, and visually appealing website.\n\n---\n\n### **Technology and Startups**\n6. **Apple** (https://www.apple.com/)  \n   - A masterclass in minimalist design, with high-quality visuals and seamless navigation.\n\n7. **Stripe** (https://stripe.com/)  \n   - A tech company with a sleek, modern design that balances professionalism and creativity.\n\n---\n\n### **Media and Publishing**\n8. **The New York Times** (https://www.nytimes.com/)  \n   - A clean, easy-to-read layout that prioritizes content and readability.\n\n9. **Medium** (https://medium.com/)  \n   - A content platform with a simple, elegant design that focuses on typography and readability.\n\n---\n\n### **Nonprofit and Social Impact**\n10. **Water.org** (https://water.org/)  \n    - A visually striking website that combines storytelling, photography, and clear calls to action.\n\n---\n\n### **Agency and Studio Websites**\n11. **Huge** (https://www.hugeinc.com/)  \n    - A digital agency with a bold, dynamic website that reflects its innovative approach.\n\n12. **DesignStudio** (https://designstudio.com/)  \n    - Known for its clean, modern design and smooth transitions.\n\n---\n\n### **Interactive and Experimental**\n13. **Bruno Simon** (https://bruno-simon.com/)  \n    - A fun, interactive portfolio where users can \"drive\" a car through a 3D environment.\n\n14. **Hello Monday** (https://www.hellomonday.com/)  \n    - An agency website that uses bold animations and creative layouts.\n\n---\n\n### **Others**\n15. **Airbnb** (https://www.airbnb.com/)  \n    - A user-focused design with stunning visuals and intuitive navigation.\n\n16. **Nowness** (https://www.nowness.com/)  \n    - A platform for video content with a visually rich, immersive design.\n\n---\n\nThese websites excel in different aspects of design, from usability and typography to interactivity and visual appeal. Exploring them can provide inspiration for your own projects!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
